description:
**Job Description:**


The roles are within the Avionic Systems – Systems Engineering team, which is a part of the Technical Disciplines Group within the Engineering Directorate.  

Avionic System Engineering is the focal point in the Engineering Department for definition, development, integration and certification of Avionics systems, such as Displays, aircraft Sensor Systems, Communication and Navigation Systems, Vehicle Monitoring Systems, Mission Systems, Role Equipments, Flight Data Recorders...  

Avionics System Engineer interfaces with all the Engineering functions, like Software Engineering, Airframe and Systems Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Electromagnetic Compatibility, Advanced Diagnostic, Airworthiness, Chief Projects offices (CPE), Experimental Department, Flight Test Engineering (FTE) and also outside the Engineering perimeter like with Program Management (PM), Procurement, Production Plants and Flight Line, Customer Support.  

The System Engineer is responsible for:  

* Avionics System requirements capture, allocation, derivation, validation and verification, and architecture definition derived from end customer operational requirements and certification requirements;
* Definition of electro\-avionics design and integration by functional schematics preparation and subsystem Interface Control Documents analysis to be used as input for aircraft installation drawings;
* Development of System Level requirements for software components;
* Conduct the Avionics System Development Lifecyle, in terms of System Requirements Review, Design Reviews, SW Requirements Reviews, Test Readiness Review, Flight Clearance and Final Qualification Reviews: prepare presentations and lead/support technical design reviews;
* Preparation of detailed equipment and systems specification and Statement of Work documentation and monitoring of supplier development and qualification activity;
* Preparation and execution of Bench Test procedures and aircraft test procedures for the Avionics systems, participate in aircraft trials, including off\-site test Ranges;
* Preparation of Certification documentation for Avionics Systems (i.e. Design Report, Ground / Flight Test Plan \& Report, Analysis, Qualification and Compliance Reports);
* Technical management of external suppliers;
* Support to Production and Customer Support for troubleshooting analysis and aircraft test execution;
* Liaison with Customers, internal and external;
* Supporting bid activities with future Customers.

Requirements:

* University Degree or equivalent in technical field: Electronic, Telecommunication, Automation, Computer, Nuclear or Electrical Engineering; Aeronautical Engineering or other scientific discipline;
* Proven background in the design, development, integration and qualification of avionics systems (civil or military);
* Familiarity with civil and/or military aerospace certification environment;
* Desirable knowledge of systems engineering tools for requirements management (e.g. IBM Rational DOORS), and Model Based System Engineering development approach (e.g. UML/SysML tools);
* Capabilities to work in cross\-functional team environments;

**Seniority:**


**Primary Location:**


IT \- Varese \- Cascina Costa**Additional Locations:**

**Contract Type:**


Permanent**Hybrid Working:**

2026/04 \| Milan
**Cogentech SRL** is a Benefit Corporation controlled by IFOM ETS, a privately held non\-profit research institute at the forefront of basic and translational cancer research. Collaboration with IFOM ensures that Cogentech’s services are always cutting\-edge.


Since 2011, Cogentech has been operating in the field of genetic testing for hereditary tumors, performing over 1,700 analyses per year using its proprietary NGS panels, OncoPan® and OncoPed®. The company invests more than 20% of its annual budget in Research \& Development to develop new tools and innovative diagnostic devices and to maintain its competitive position in the market.


Cogentech is committed to delivering high\-quality services, not only by adhering to strict certification standards but also through the continuous training of its highly skilled staff. The company fosters a safe and inclusive work environment, grounded in mutual respect and diversity, providing equal opportunities to all qualified individuals.


**We are seeking for our company:** **In vivo imaging technician**


The Biological Research Facility manages a state\-of\-the\-art mouse facility where mice are housed and bred to support a wide range of research programs. The facility operates with a strong commitment to the application of the 3Rs principles (Replacement, Reduction, Refinement), with particular attention to the highest standards of animal welfare.


Within the unit, and reporting to the Head of the Facility, we are seeking to recruit an experienced technician dedicated to in vivo imaging activities, with a focus on MRI and micro\-CT technologies.


**About the position**


The technician will play a key role in the daily operations and development of a newly established in vivo imaging service, equipped with a compact MRI and a micro\-CT scanner, supporting a broad range of preclinical research activities.


The main responsibilities will include:


* Preparing animals for imaging procedures in accordance with established protocols and welfare standards;
* Performing MRI and micro\-CT image acquisition, ensuring high\-quality and reproducible data;
* Overseeing routine maintenance, quality control, and proper functioning of imaging equipment;
* Supporting researchers in image processing and analysis, facilitating effective use of imaging data;
* Contributing to the implementation and optimization of workflows and standard operating procedures;
* Ensuring compliance with institutional policies, regulatory requirements, and the 3Rs principles;


**Required Skills**


* Extensive experience working with laboratory mice, ensuring the highest standards of animal welfare and adherence to 3Rs principles;
* Fulfillment of the requirements to perform functions (a) and (d) pursuant to Article 23, paragraph 2, of Legislative Decree 26/2014;
* Previous experience with in vivo imaging techniques, including MRI and micro\-CT;
* Familiarity with imaging data analysis and software tools used in preclinical research;
* Ability to follow and contribute to the development of standard operating procedures (SOPs) and optimized workflows;


**Education**


The candidate should hold a degree in Biological Sciences, Biotechnology, Veterinary Medicine, or a related field.


**Languages**


Fluent Italian, spoken and written;


Excellent spoken and written English;


**Soft Skills**


* Strong teamwork;
* Excellent communication skills and strong analytical mindset;
* Goal\-oriented approach with special attention to established timelines;
* Capacity to face tight deadlines and handle stress conditions;
* A flexible and problem\-solving approach to work effectively in response to changing demands;
* Work at exceptionally high levels of accuracy and attention to detail;
* Timeliness and accuracy;


**What we offer**


The successful candidate will have the opportunity to work in a friendly, collaborative and innovative team, in an international work environment with a flexible schedule.


* Agreements with discounts for gym, pharmacy, and various shops around our institute;
* Bar and canteen inside the campus \& lunch benefit;
* Company nursery;
* Continuous support to candidates and their families (including housing, schooling, registration to the national health system, work permits, etc.) thanks to the activities of the Welcome Office;
* Medical service;
* Laptop;
* CAF service – tax declaration;
* Life and medical insurance;


**Type of Contract:** Permanent contract, full time;


**Location:** Milan \- Scalo di Porta Romana area


**Contacts Details:** If you are interested in this opportunity, please submit your CV and a letter of interest to: alberto.gobbi@cogentech.it




This announcement is addressed to both sexes pursuant to Laws 903/77 and 125/91 and to people of all ages and nationalities pursuant to Legislative Decrees 215/03 and 216/03\.


**Disclaimer privacy**


(Article 13 of the EU Regulation 2016/679\) We inform you that the archiving and processing of data referring to you are carried out by IFOM \- Istituto Fondazione di Oncologia Molecolare ETS in order to perform the recruitment process. Pursuant to Article 6(1\)(b), the legal basis for the processing is the necessity to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract. Your data shall be communicated to third parties that could be located in countries outside the European Union for the recruitment process. IFOM has obtained the necessary guarantees to transfer the data in compliance with the provisions of Chapter V of the GDPR.


The resumes received will be deleted at the end of the calendar year following the one of receipt; if you are still interested in proposing your application, you will have to re\-send it.


According to Article 15 et seq. of the EU Regulation 2016/679, to exercise your rights you can write to the Data Controller: IFOM \- Istituto Fondazione di Oncologia Molecolare ETS, via Adamello 16, Milano, privacy\-desk@ifom.eu.


Finally, we inform you that IFOM has appointed a Data Protection Officer (DPO) who can be contacted at dpo@ifom.eu.



last update: 09/04/26

IRCCS San Raffaele Scientific Institute in Milan, Italy, is looking for Postdoctoral fellow to join the Infections and Cystic Fibrosis Unit, Division of Immunology, Transplantation and Infectious Diseases.



The candidate will contribute to a Telethon\-funded project investigating inter\-organ communication between lung infection/inflammation and gut involvement. We will use Collaborative Cross (CC) mice with Cystic Fibrosis Transmembrane Conductance Regulator (CFTR) mutation to model cystic fibrosis and study gut–lung crosstalk.



**About the Lab and Group:** Alessandra Bragonzi’s group at IRCCS San Raffaele Institute.



**Focus: Integration of basic and preclinical research to:**  

understand the genetic and molecular determinants of host–pathogen interactions during initial and persistent bacterial infections;

define new approaches to treat infections and inflammation in respiratory diseases.



**Responsibilities:**  

design and execute in vivo and in vitro experiments related to lung–gut axis;

analyze immunological, microbiological, and omics data;

interpret and integrate data from the mouse model with data from people with cystic fibrosis;

collaborate with a multidisciplinary team and engage with diverse stakeholders, including patients.



**Who we are looking for:**  

PhD in immunology, microbiology, genetics, or a related biomedical field;

experience with animal models and flow cytometry is a plus;

highly motivated and committed to developing a research career;



**Work details:**  

a funded, contract\-based position dependent on research experience and CV;

starting date is immediate and the position will remain open until filled;

**place of work:** IRCCS San Raffaele Hospital, Via Olgettina, number 60 \- Milan (Italy).



At San Raffaele Scientific Institute, a world\-renowned center of excellence for clinical and scientific activities, we believe that considering diversity and promoting an open and inclusive environment is crucial to our success. We are committed to ensure that equal employment opportunities are provided and based on merit without regard to age, religion, sex, disability, medical condition, sexual orientation, cultural and social backgrounds, gender identity or expression, national or ethnic origin, or any other legally recognized status entitled to protection under applicable laws. We offer attractive conditions and rewards appropriate to an internationally competitive research organization.
